712365f-b.text:
(1)
West 38th Street, south side, west from Dyer to Terth Avenues, showing the vesterly half of that Ninth to Tenth Avenues block, that has been bisected by this new thoroughfare, the entrance to the lLincoln Tunnel. Two churches appear here, which are the Roman Catholic Church of St. Chiara (St. Clare) and a German
Lutheran Chapel.
Feb. 10, 1938.
P. L. Sperr,
(2) and (3)
An eastward view across Dver Avenue with the Empire State Bldg. in the background. In the foreground of this view and No. 3 is the
aforementioned Chapel at No. 446, a former stable.
Peb. 10, 1938.
P. L. Sperr,
